{"title_page": "Olesoxime", "text_new": "{{Drugbox\n| drug_name = \n| IUPAC_name        = (NZ)-N-[(8S,9S,10R,13R,14S,17R)-10,13-dimethyl-17-[(2R)-6-methylheptan-2-yl]-1,2,6,7,8,9,11,12,14,15,16,17-dodecahydrocyclopenta[a]phenanthren-3-ylidene]hydroxylamine\n| image             = Olesoxime.svg\n| alt               = \n| caption           = \n<!--Clinical data -->\n| tradename         = \n| Drugs.com         = \n| MedlinePlus       = \n| pregnancy_AU      = <!-- A / B1 / B2 / B3 / C / D / X -->\n| pregnancy_US      = <!-- A / B            / C / D / X -->\n| pregnancy_category= \n| legal_AU = <!-- S2, S3, S4, S5, S6, S7, S8, S9 or Unscheduled-->\n| legal_CA = <!-- OTC, Rx-only, Schedule I, II, III, IV, V, VI, VII, VIII -->\n| legal_UK = <!-- GSL, P, POM, CD, CD Lic, CD POM, CD No Reg POM, CD (Benz) POM, CD (Anab) POM or CD Inv POM -->\n| legal_US = <!-- OTC / Rx-only / Schedule I, II, III, IV, V -->\n| legal_status      = \n| routes_of_administration = \n<!--Pharmacokinetic data -->\n| bioavailability   = \n| protein_bound     = \n| metabolism        = \n| elimination_half-life = \n| excretion         = \n<!--Identifiers -->\n| CAS_number        = \t 22033-87-0\n| UNII_Ref = {{fdacite|correct|FDA}}\n| UNII = A6778U5IFY\n| ATCvet            = \n| ATC_prefix        = <!-- 'none' if uncategorised -->\n| ATC_suffix        = \n| PubChem           =  21763506\n| DrugBank          = \n| KEGG           =  D11213\n| ChemSpiderID      = 23350363\n<!-- Chemical data -->\n| C=27 | H=45 | N=1 | O=1\n| molecular_weight  = 399.65\n| smiles            = C[C@H](CCCC(C)C)[C@H]1CC[C@@H]2[C@@]1(CC[C@H]3[C@H]2CCC4=C/C(=N\\O)/CC[C@]34C)C\n| StdInChI          = 1S/C27H45NO/c1-18(2)7-6-8-19(3)23-11-12-24-22-10-9-20-17-21(28-29)13-15-26(20,4)25(22)14-16-27(23,24)5/h17-19,22-25,29H,6-16H2,1-5H3/t19-,22+,23-,24+,25+,26+,27-/m1/s1\n| StdInChIKey       = QNTASHOAVRSLMD-GYKMGIIDSA-N\n}}\n\n'''Olesoxime''' ('''TRO19622''') is an [[experimental drug]] formerly under development by the now-defunct French company [[Trophos]] as a treatment for a range of [[Neuromuscular disease|neuromuscular disorders]]. It has a [[cholesterol]]-like structure and belongs to the [[cholesterol]]-[[oxime]] family of [[mitochondrial pore modulator]]s.<ref name=\"pmid20721828\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Martin LJ | title = Olesoxime, a cholesterol-like neuroprotectant for the potential treatment of amyotrophic lateral sclerosis | journal = IDrugs | volume = 13 | issue = 8 | pages = 568\u201380 | date = August 2010 | pmid = 20721828 | pmc = 3058503 | doi =  }}</ref><ref name=\"urlolesoxime () UKMi New Drugs Online Database\">{{cite web | url = http://www.ukmi.nhs.uk/applications/ndo/record_view_open.asp?newDrugID=5002 | title = Olesoxime | work = New Drugs Online Report | publisher = UK Medicines Information | access-date = }}</ref>\n\n==Research==\nIn preclinical studies, the compound displayed [[Neuroprotection|neuroprotective]] properties by promoting the function and survival of neurons and other cell types under disease-relevant stress conditions. It did so through interactions with the [[mitochondrial permeability transition pore]] (mPTP).<ref name=\"JPET\">{{cite journal|vauthors=Bordet T, Buisson B, Michaud M, Drouot C, Gal\u00e9a P, Delaage P, Akentieva NP, Evers AS, Covey DF, Ostuni MA, Lacap\u00e8re JJ, Massaad C, Schumacher M, Steidl EM, Maux D, Delaage M, Henderson CE, Pruss RM|date=August 2007|title=Identification and characterization of cholest-4-en-3-one, oxime (TRO19622), a novel drug candidate for amyotrophic lateral sclerosis|journal=The Journal of Pharmacology and Experimental Therapeutics|volume=322|issue=2|pages=709\u201320|doi=10.1124/jpet.107.123000|pmc=|pmid=17496168}}</ref>\n\nA 2009\u20132011 phase 3 [[clinical trial]] in [[amyotrophic lateral sclerosis]] did not demonstrate an increase in survival.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.trophos.com/news/pr20111213.htm|title=Trophos announces results of phase 3 study of olesoxime in Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis|last=|first=|date=2011-12-13|work=Press Release|publisher=Trophos|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223171439/http://www.trophos.com:80/news/pr20111213.htm|archive-date=2014-02-23|access-date=}}</ref> A 2011\u20132013 trial in [[spinal muscular atrophy]] (SMA) indicated that the compound may prevent deterioration of muscle function.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.trophos.com/news/pr20140310.htm|title=Trophos announces top-line results of pivotal trial of olesoxime in spinal muscular atrophy|last=|first=|date=2014-03-10|work=Press Release|publisher=Trophos|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141211081147/http://www.trophos.com:80/news/pr20140310.htm|archive-date=2014-12-11|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Bertini E, Dessaud E, Mercuri E, Muntoni F, Kirschner J, Reid C, Lusakowska A, Comi GP, Cuisset JM, Abitbol JL, Scherrer B, Ducray PS, Buchbjerg J, Vianna E, van der Pol WL, Vuillerot C, Blaettler T, Fontoura P | title = Safety and efficacy of olesoxime in patients with type 2 or non-ambulatory type 3 spinal muscular atrophy: a randomised, double-blind, placebo-controlled phase 2 trial | journal = The Lancet. Neurology | volume = 16 | issue = 7 | pages = 513\u2013522 | date = July 2017 | pmid = 28460889 | doi = 10.1016/S1474-4422(17)30085-6 | url = http://discovery.ucl.ac.uk/10067958/3/Bertini_Olesoxime%20Ph2_Revised_160117.pdf }}</ref> In 2015, the entire olesoxime programme was purchased by [[Hoffmann-La Roche]] for \u20ac120 million with a view to developing a treatment for SMA. However, in June 2018, faced with technical and regulatory challenges and competition from a potentially more effective drug [[nusinersen]], Roche halted further development of olesoxime.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fiercebiotech.com/biotech/roche-scraps-eu120m-sma-drug-after-hitting-many-difficulties|title=Roche scraps \u20ac120M SMA drug after hitting \u2018many difficulties\u2019|last=Taylor|first=Nick P.|date=2018-06-01|website=www.fiercebiotech.com|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2018-06-07}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Rovini A, Carr\u00e9 M, Bordet T, Pruss RM, Braguer D | title = Olesoxime prevents microtubule-targeting drug neurotoxicity: selective preservation of EB comets in differentiated neuronal cells | journal = Biochemical Pharmacology | volume = 80 | issue = 6 | pages = 884\u201394 | date = September 2010 | pmid = 20417191 | pmc =  | doi = 10.1016/j.bcp.2010.04.018 }}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Xiao WH, Zheng FY, Bennett GJ, Bordet T, Pruss RM | title = Olesoxime (cholest-4-en-3-one, oxime): analgesic and neuroprotective effects in a rat model of painful peripheral neuropathy produced by the chemotherapeutic agent, paclitaxel | journal = Pain | volume = 147 | issue = 1-3 | pages = 202\u20139 | date = December 2009 | pmid = 19833436 | pmc = 2787910 | doi = 10.1016/j.pain.2009.09.006 }}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Bordet T, Buisson B, Michaud M, Abitbol JL, Marchand F, Grist J, Andriambeloson E, Malcangio M, Pruss RM | title = Specific antinociceptive activity of cholest-4-en-3-one, oxime (TRO19622) in experimental models of painful diabetic and chemotherapy-induced neuropathy | journal = The Journal of Pharmacology and Experimental Therapeutics | volume = 326 | issue = 2 | pages = 623\u201332 | date = August 2008 | pmid = 18492948 | pmc =  | doi = 10.1124/jpet.108.139410 }}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{MeSH name|cholest-4-en-3-one,%20oxime|3=cholest-4-en-3-one, oxime}}'\n\n[[Category:Drugs with unknown mechanisms of action]]\n[[Category:Cholestanes]]\n[[Category:Ketoximes]]\n[[Category:Hoffmann-La Roche brands]]\n[[Category:Spinal muscular atrophy]]\n", "text_old": "{{Drugbox\n| drug_name = \n| IUPAC_name        = (NZ)-N-[(8S,9S,10R,13R,14S,17R)-10,13-dimethyl-17-[(2R)-6-methylheptan-2-yl]-1,2,6,7,8,9,11,12,14,15,16,17-dodecahydrocyclopenta[a]phenanthren-3-ylidene]hydroxylamine\n|