st quality cotton in India and even attracted Birlas to set up a mill which still exists today in the town, but after 1995 the produce took a deep dip and people shifted to other cash crops. Today it is known in the area to have most fertile land supporting thousands of acre under horticulture especially the kinnow which is exported to west Asia.{{cn|date= August 2017}}\n\n==Sri Karanpur Market==\nSri Karanpur, also known as Mandi Karanpur is famous for dealing of various crops namely cotton, barley and wheat.\nThe old mandi now a Bazaar famous among many nearby villages consists of many cloths, jewelers, restaurants and Sweets shops. Nagpal Sweet House is one of the oldest and most famous Sweet shop famous among many people from districts of Rajasthan, Punjab and Delhi.and a bazaar of vegetables. There is a frequent area of selling vegetables by bid system.\n\n==Transportation==\n\nSubhash Chander Bhatheja is a very famous    ( 40 years old ) Bus Transporter At Sri Karanpur .His Firm's name Is Subhash Motors . Mr.Subhash G Is A Down To Earth Personality With The Knowledge Of Entire Indian Roads ( Villages ,Tehsils ,Districts ,States )  . He Has more  Knowledge Than Google Regarding Transports .You Can Call To Him At Their Personal Phone Numbers for Advices and  Buses Bookings ,Trucks Etc  = 9413934447 , 7504371313 ...  \n\n\nBy Train - there is direct train from [[Delhi Sarai Rohilla railway station]] [DEE] to Sri Karanpur. Train no 12455/56 [[Delhi Sarai rohila]]  to [[Bikaner]] superfast express and from Sri Ganganagar few passenger trains to Suratgarh goes via Sri Karanpur. The train come from [[Hanumangarh jn.]] to here\n\nTrain no.17623/24 [[Srigangangar]] to [[Hajur Sahib Nanded]] weekliy superfast via [[Suratgarh]] [[Bikaner]]  [[Ahmedabad]] [[Vadodara]] \n\nTrain no. 54761 [[hanumangarh]] to [[Suratgarh]] via [[Sri Ganganagar]]\n \ntrain no. 16311/12 [[Sri Ganganagar]] to [[kochuwali (kerla)]] weekliy superfast train\n\nBy Bus - There is single direct bus t